Class ComplexValuedVectorState

java.lang.Object
  cellularAutomata.cellState.model.CellState
      cellularAutomata.cellState.model.ComplexValuedVectorState

public class ComplexValuedVectorState
extends CellState

A vector state of any length with any Complex values, represented as an array of Complex numbers.

ComplexValuedVectorState

public ComplexValuedVectorState(Complex[] state,
                                Complex[] alternateState,
                                Complex[] emptyState,
                                Complex[] fullState,
                                double minRandom,
                                double maxRandom)
Create a Complex vector state from an array of Complex numbers, and use the specified view to display the vectors.

Parameters:
state - The vector of complex values (as an array).
alternateState - An alternate state supplied by the user that will be drawn with a right click.
emptyState - An empty state supplied by the user. Usually a vector of 0+0i, or minimum values, but may be a vector of any complex numbers.
fullState - A vector of usually a maximum values, but may be a vector of any complex values.
minRandom - The minimum value that each of the real and imaginary components can take when constructing a random vector. Used by the method getRandomState().
maxRandom - The maximum value that each of the real and imaginary components can take when constructing a random vector. Used by the method getRandomState().
Method Detail

clone

public CellState clone()
Creates a clone of this cellState; this method must return a different instance of the cell state, but with all the same values.

The intent is that, for any CellState x, the expression: x.clone() != x will be true, and that the expression: x.clone().getClass() == x.getClass() will be true. Also: x.clone().equals(x) will be true.

(Note this method is used in places where we need a copy of the cell's state but that the same instance would cause unpredictable or incorrect behavior.)

Specified by:
clone in class CellState
Returns:
A unique copy of the cell's state (must not return "this" object).
